Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
, f. Suppl. 307. 1781. “ 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7B59FC892255FCCD" box="[780,1295,842,869]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">in Madera in Horto Monasteri Sti. Francisci</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7D75FC8922F6FCCC" box="[1312,1452,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">F. Masson”.</emphasis>
NON 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7899FCAC260EFC21" author="Miller, P." box="[204,340,878,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref19811" refString="Miller, P. (1768) The gardeners dictionary: containing the best and newest methods of cultivating and improving the kitchen, fruit, flower garden, and nursery, as also for performing the practical parts of agriculture, including the management of vineyards, with the methods of making and preserving wine, according to the present practice of the most skilful vignerons in the several wine countries in Europe, together with directions for propagating and improving, from real practice and experience, all sorts of timber trees, ed. 8. Printed for the author, London, without pagination." type="book" year="1768">Miller 1768</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7E164F78E8FC50249BFABD" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7E164F78E8FC5025E3FB95" blockId="14.[136,1452,698,1732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8FC50269BFC05" bold="true" box="[189,449,914,940]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F798BFC5025E5FC05" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[478,703,914,940]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas (2003)</bibRefCitation>
chose the collection of Commerson in 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7E164F7CDCFC502269FC05" box="[1161,1331,914,940]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, deposited in the herbarium P, as 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7E164F79C6FC7426A7FC79" box="[403,509,950,976]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">lectotype</typeStatus>
. However, there are 
<specimenCount id="11E0FD040B7E164F7AA7FC7424FAFC79" box="[754,928,950,976]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
of this collection in P herbarium. Therefore, according to Art. 9.17, of the International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7CE1FC1822CAFC5D" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[1204,1424,986,1012]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref20537" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7D40FC192214FC5D" box="[1301,1358,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
) a second step of lectotypification was necessary. The specimen P barcode 02273667 was chosen as 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7E164F7C9BFC3C226FFBB1" box="[1230,1333,1022,1048]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">lectotype</typeStatus>
because it is more representative, with the presence of fruits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7E164F78E8FB84249BFABD" blockId="14.[136,1452,698,1732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8FB8426D4FBC9" bold="true" box="[189,398,1094,1120]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F79FEFB8425D3FBC9" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[427,649,1094,1120]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas (2003)</bibRefCitation>
creates the section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7B37FB8424A0FBC9" box="[866,1018,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Distichifoliae</emphasis>
and presents a taxonomic study of this section. Before this study, many authors treated the species in this section as belonging to a few polymorphic species, as in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F791DFB4C2578FB00" authority="Burman" authorityName="Burman" authorityYear="1768" box="[328,546,1166,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F791DFB4C269AFB01" box="[328,448,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida acuta</emphasis>
Burman
</taxonomicName>
f. (1768: 147)(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7A99FB4C243FFB01" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[716,869,1166,1193]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 522" refId="ref18772" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1988) Malvaceae of Mexico. Systematic Botany Monograph 25: 1 - 522. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25027717" type="journal article" year="1988">Fryxell 1988</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7B24FB4D233EFB00" author="Fuertes Aguilar, J." box="[881,1124,1166,1193]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref18839" refString="Fuertes Aguilar, J. (1995) Sida L. (Malvaceae). In: Piedrahita, S. D., Telleria, M. T., Castroviejo, S., Mejia, W. J., Carranza, P. R., Contreras, G. L. (Eds.) Flora de Colombia, No. 17. Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota, 142 pp." type="book" year="1995">Fuertes Aguilar 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F7CA0FB4C22F1FB01" authorityName="Cavanilles" authorityYear="1785" box="[1269,1451,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="planicaulis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7CA0FB4C22F1FB01" box="[1269,1451,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida planicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can often be found identified as 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F79AEFB71250CFB65" authorityName="Burman" authorityYear="1768" box="[507,598,1203,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F79AEFB71250CFB65" box="[507,598,1203,1229]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">S. acuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in herbaria. 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F7ABCFB7024C5FB65" authorityName="Cavanilles" authorityYear="1785" box="[745,927,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="planicaulis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7ABCFB7024C5FB65" box="[745,927,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida planicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other species of section 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78DDFB14267AFB59" box="[136,288,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Distichifoliae</emphasis>
by the presence of 7–8 mericarps, aristae 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7E164F7B50FB142412FB58" box="[773,840,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, flowers in axilar glomerules, yellowish corolla, staminal tube glabrous (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F79C1FB38256BFABD" box="[404,561,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. A–D. Sida nemorensis. A. Flower. B. Branch with leaves and flowers. C. Leaves and schizocarps. D. Calyx and mericarps. E–J. Sida paradoxa. E. Flower. F. Branch with leaves and stipules. G. Abaxial surface of leaf. H. Habit. I–J. Schizocarps. K–P. Sida planicaulis. K. Flowers. L. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Branch with distichous leaves arrangement. O. Schizocarps. P. Branch with flowers and schizocarps. PhotographsA–B by Amaury Junior, C–P by Martin Grings (C–D from Krapovickas &amp; Cristóbal 38480, HAS)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415499/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Figures 6K–P</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F7A69FB382536FABD" box="[572,620,1274,1300]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">14L</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7E164F7A22FB382592FABD" box="[631,712,1274,1300]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7AB7FB3824EFFABD" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[738,949,1274,1300]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7E164F78E8FADC233EFA45" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7E164F78E8FADC233EFA45" blockId="14.[136,1452,698,1732]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8FADC25B2FA91" bold="true" box="[189,744,1310,1336]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7E164F7C5EFADC2320FA91" box="[1035,1146,1310,1336]" name="Argentina" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(Misiones), and 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7E164F7D15FADC22DDFA91" box="[1344,1415,1310,1336]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in northeast, southeast, midwest and south (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7A19FA80247CFAF5" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[588,806,1346,1372]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7AFAFA8125BCFAF5" box="[687,742,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F7B65FA8024E5FAF5" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[816,959,1346,1372]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The species expanded to Indian and Pacific Oceans regions (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F791DFAA42544FA29" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[328,542,1382,1408]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="83 - 121" refId="ref19352" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2003) Sida seccion Distichifolia (Monteiro) Krapov. comb. nov., stat. nov. (Malvaceae-Malveae). Bonplandia 12: 83 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 121 - 41407" type="journal article" year="2003">Krapovickas 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7E164F7AE7FAA424D1FA29" box="[690,907,1382,1408]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in Inland subtropical forest, Coastal subtropical Forest and Tropical Forest (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7E164F7AC1FA4825AEFA0C" box="[660,756,1418,1445]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Figure 5</figureCitation>
), in edges of Forests and in ruderal shaded environments, from 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7E164F78DDFA6C2658FA60" box="[136,258,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" unit="m" value="200.0" valueMax="400.0" valueMin="0.0">0 to 400 m</quantity>
of elevation. 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F79C8FA6C2509FA61" authorityName="Cavanilles" authorityYear="1785" box="[413,595,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="planicaulis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F79C8FA6C2509FA61" box="[413,595,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida planicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered Least Concern (LC) because it has large EOO and AOO, since it is a frequent and often ruderal species and is present in more than one continent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
